included.description:
Hacking Health is an international movement designed to improve health care by inviting technology creators and health care professionals to collaborate on realistic, human-centric solutions to front-line problems.

Hacking Health is a weekend-long hackathon from May 1st - 3rd 2015 where doctors, nurses, administrators, researchers, managers, designers and developers will come together to collaborate, dream up & design apps for patient-centric care.
included.title: Hacking Health - Best Student Idea & People's Choice Award

included.description: The Hemsley Challenge is a corporate-wide innovation event in which employees are asked to tackle topics that help UnitedHealth Group advance and improve health care for the people it serves. My idea fits the theme of "Decide, Deploy, Follow through with Intelligent Urgency" and means to intelligently increase UHG's responsiveness to its members' support needs in a way that addresses these challenges before they evolve into costly crises.

included.description:
Translate business and technical requirements into functional specifications through annotated prototypes and wireframes

Create visual design systems and guidelines for the new version of the responsive site and mobile app
